  "canonical_term": "Short Position Tool",
  "aliases": [],
  "school": "General",
  "definition": "A TradingView drawing tool used to plan a short trade by marking entry price, stop-loss level, and profit target, while displaying the risk-to-reward ratio.",
  "identification_rules": [
    "Click the 'Forecasting and Measurement Tools' menu and select 'Short Position'.",
    "Click on the chart at the intended entry price to place the tool.",
    "Drag the stop-loss level to a price above the entry (e.g., above a resistance or swing high).",
    "Drag the target level downward to set a profit target based on the desired risk-to-reward ratio (e.g., 3:1)."
  ],
  "trading_implication": "This tool helps traders plan short trades by defining entry, stop-loss, and target levels with a clear risk-to-reward ratio. It provides a visual framework for risk management, ensuring that the potential profit is at least a multiple of the risk taken (commonly 3:1).",
